{{Quote|Some of our earliest thoughts on the atlas and galactic geography were shaped by the contributions of Eric "Cartographer" Przybylski.|[[Daniel Wallace]] and [[Jason Fry]], in the Author's Acknowledgments to ''[[The Essential Atlas]]''|<ref name="TEA">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref>}}
'''Eric Przybylski''', also known as "Cartographer," is the creator of the now-defunct website '''Nav-Computer.com''', an effort to assemble all the various planets, systems, sectors, routes, and nebulae across [[The galaxy/Legends|the ''Star Wars'' galaxy]]. He created maps of the galaxy and specific regions of it in great detail, using hundreds of sources of [[Star Wars Legends|Expanded Universe]] material and all canon from the movies. The site also had a systems section that detailed planetary positions within each referenced system.<ref name="Archived site">{{WebCite|url=http://www.nav-computer.com|text=Nav Computer|author=Przybylski, Eric|archivedate=20061020203929}}</ref>

On [[April 12]], [[2007]], Cartographer noted on the forums at [[StarWars.com]] that he had lost the Nav-Computer.com URL, and that the site was without a home, though he still retained all of his data and did not rule out an eventual relaunch.<ref name="TOS message">{{SWBoards|url=thread.jspa?threadID=118855&start=1411|thread=Galaxy Map Discussion|user=cartographer@nav-computer.com|nobackup=1}}</ref>

Though the site has not reappeared, Przybylski's early and detailed contributions to ''Star Wars'' cartography shaped the ideas of other authors, including [[Daniel Wallace]] and [[Jason Fry]], who acknowledged those contributions in ''[[The Essential Atlas]]''.<ref name="TEA" />

